          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-26-1697120803863-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-28-1697120808058-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-28-1697120808058-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-28-1697120808058-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-28-1697120808058-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-28-1697120808058-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-27-1697120812560-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-27-1697120812560-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-27-1697120812560-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-27-1697120812560-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-27-1697120812560-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, roughly chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>sweet pointed pepper[s]</strong> into rounds</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>free range chicken thighs</strong> into strips</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-26-1697120816183-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-26-1697120816183-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-26-1697120816183-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-26-1697120816183-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-26-1697120816183-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>ras el hanout</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>chopped ginger </strong>and<strong> garlic</strong>, <strong>diced apricots </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2 min or until the garlic has softened, then add the <strong>chicken strips</strong> and cook for a further 3-4 min</p><p>Add your <strong>chopped tomato</strong>,<strong> pepper rounds</strong>, <strong>chicken stock</strong> and the juice of <strong>half </strong>your<strong> lemon[s]</strong> and cook, covered, for 8-10 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your<strong> Moroccan-style free range chicken thigh & apricot tagine</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-24-1697120819996-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-24-1697120819996-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-24-1697120819996-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-24-1697120819996-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-24-1697120819996-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the tagine is cooking, chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Fluff the <strong>couscous </strong>with a fork and add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lemon juice</strong></p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>with<strong> </strong>a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the<strong> chopped parsley</strong> (save the rest for later!) and mix everything together – this is your <strong>herby couscous</strong></p><p>Stir the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped parsley</strong> through the<strong> Moroccan-style free range chicken thigh & apricot tagine</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-14-1697120823555-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-14-1697120823555-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-14-1697120823555-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-14-1697120823555-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-14-1697120823555-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Moroccan-style free range chicken thigh & apricot tagine</strong> with the <strong>herby couscous </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>flaked almonds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
